===Etymology===
Old French ''almanach'' < Medieval Latin ''almanachus'' < Hispano-Arabic ''almanak'' (almanac, calendar) < Arabic {{ARchar|[[مناخ|المناخ]]}} (''al-manāx'', climate), possibly from Late {{Gr.}} [[αλμενιχιακά]] (calendar), probably ultimately of Coptic origin. Possibly the central syllable '''-man-''' is cognate with [[moon]] and [[month]], or was influenced by Proto-Indo-European '''*me(n)ses-''' (moon, month) < PIE base '''*me-''' (to measure).

===Noun===
